{% capture default_body_html %}
  <h2>What This Preview Is For</h2>
  <p>This site acts as a single-product launch preview for one copper pour-over kettle. It is designed to clarify the object, the current boundaries, and the only live action: product updates.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>The homepage frames the stage, the object, and the update sign-up.</li>
    <li>The product details page explains the version, the listed specs, and the notify-only boundary.</li>
    <li>The FAQ answers the questions that typically create purchase confusion too early.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What The Frontstage Surface Shows</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Surface</th>
        <th>Current role</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <th>Homepage</th>
        <td>Sets the tone, reduces misread, and routes people to product details or the update form.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <th>Product details</th>
        <td>Shows the non-silver-lined version, the listed specs, and the current notify-only boundary.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <th>FAQ</th>
        <td>Answers what is live now, what is not, and what email sign-up actually means.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <th>Notify form</th>
        <td>Captures low-commitment product updates only. It does not create a reservation or purchase path.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>What Stays Offstage Until Review</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Pricing, availability, shipping timing, and any live commerce promise</li>
    <li>Preorder, waitlist, reservation, or early-access language</li>
    <li>Performance, certification, or safety claims</li>
    <li>Final measured details and approved close-up photography</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What Signing Up Means</h2>
  <p>Leaving an email means you want product updates only. It does not reserve inventory, hold a place, or create a purchase obligation.</p>
{% endcapture %}

{% capture aside_html %}
  <span class="preview-doc__tag">Product Preview</span>
  <span class="preview-doc__tag">Notify Only</span>
  <span class="preview-doc__tag">Single Product</span>
  <p>This page exists to reduce confusion, not to create sales pressure.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/pages/copper-kettle-preview">Product Details</a></li>
    <li><a href="/pages/faq">FAQ</a></li>
    <li><a href="{{ routes.root_url }}">Home</a></li>
  </ul>
{% endcapture %}

{% render 'preview-page-shell',
  eyebrow: 'Preview Terms',
  title: 'Launch Boundaries for This Preview',
  intro: 'This site is not operating as a live sales store. Its job is to introduce one product clearly, keep the boundaries visible, and route interest into updates only.',
  page_title: page.title,
  page_content: page.content,
  body_html: default_body_html,
  aside_title: 'Frontstage Checks',
  aside_html: aside_html,
  cta_title: 'See the product page with these boundaries applied',
  cta_text: 'The product details page shows the same preview terms inside the actual single-product surface.',
